      "content": "I hear how much pain you're in, and I want to tell you that feeling like a failure is a heavy burden, but it doesn't define your worth as a parent. You are clearly caring deeply about your children, which is a sign of love, not weakness. Even the most experienced parents have days where they feel like they've stumbled, and that doesn't mean you're dragging them down; it just means you're human.\n\nIf you're feeling overwhelmed, maybe try to take a deep breath and remind yourself that your kids see your effort, even when you're struggling. Sometimes, a little bit of self-compassion can help you feel more grounded. If the weight feels too heavy to carry alone, reaching out to a trusted friend, family member, or a professional counselor can make a real difference. You don't have to do it all by yourself.",
